description.plain:
William Henry Victor Schultz (b. January 28, 1997), better known by his stage name Sueco (previously Sueco The Child), is an American rapper and producer coming from Los Angeles, California.

Sueco started gaining attention by uploading various videos on Instagram of him making beats out of many different things, but he didn’t reach the mainstream attention until his hit single “fast” (originally released on April 1, 2019) blew up out of no where due to it going viral on TikTok.

On May 22, 2019, Sueco signed to the major record label, Atlantic Records.

Four months later, Sueco released his project MISCREANT on September 20, 2019, two years after releasing his 2017 project TrippyNights.

songs.title: ​fast

description.plain:
“fast” is the breakout single by Californian producer and rapper Sueco. The song did not gain much traction until it went viral on social media platform TikTok.

The song has inspired nearly one million TikTok videos, blowing it up into a mainstream hit, similarly to how the Atlanta duo iLOVEFRiDAY’s hit song “Mia Khalifa” and Lil Nas X’s “Old Town Road” had.

This sudden success of this song would eventually get Sueco signed to Atlantic Records.

songs.title: Paralyzed

description.plain:
“Paralyzed” is the highly-anticipated release by rapper and singer, Sueco. This is his second attempt at a rock song, following “SOS” with Travis Barker. In the song, Sueco sings about his toxic relationship with his significant-other and how he doesn’t want it to end even though it makes him feel terrible.

The song was first previewed on Sueco’s TikTok through a skit where Sueco showed off that he’s much more than just the “fast” rapper people know him for, explaining in the caption:

when a dude pulls up to the studio and sounds nothing like how you expect him to

The video instantly went viral, getting over twenty-five million views within the first day. Sueco then uploaded a follow-up video giving fans a pre-save link for the track and thanking them for blowing the snippet up.

On August 11, 2021, Sueco posted another video to his TikTok showing a voicemail his received from his label saying how they weren’t too keen on releasing the song as they didn’t think his audience wanted to hear a rock song from him. This song marks a change in Sueco’s career as it proves to his label and the world that he’s much more than just a “mumble rapper.”
